@{
    ViewBag.Title = "webgl";
}

<h1>WebGL</h1>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col">
        <p>
            I've always had a fascination with computer graphics.  Over the years I've dabbled in OpenGL and
            3D tools like Blender but never got to a point where I was any good at it.  I hope to change that
            and the links on this page are some of the things I've built as I try to learn.
        </p>
        <p>
            To this end, the samples below leverage the <a href="http://threejs.org/">ThreeJS</a> library which helps make
            WebGL more approachable.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header">
                <strong class="card-title">Demos</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <a class="list-group-item" asp-controller="webgl" asp-action="cube">Rotating Cube</a>
                <a class="list-group-item" asp-controller="webgl" asp-action="text">Rotating Text</a>
                <a class="list-group-item" asp-controller="webgl" asp-action="shader">Custom Shader</a>
                <a class="list-group-item" asp-controller="webgl" asp-action="blendermodel">Blender Model</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
